<subSubSection id="EA9EDA8EFF91FFB60CEAFA0DFDC9F9A5" box="[151,638,1513,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB60CEAFA0DFDC9F9A5" blockId="1.[151,638,1513,1540]" box="[151,638,1513,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<heading id="F9733E69FF91FFB60CEAFA0DFDC9F9A5" bold="true" box="[151,638,1513,1540]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" reason="1">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB60CEAFA0DFDC9F9A5" bold="true" box="[151,638,1513,1540]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
Key to species of 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF91FFB60D13FA0DFDC9F9A5" authority="Kieffer" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[366,638,1513,1540]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB60D13FA0DFDABF9A2" bold="true" box="[366,540,1513,1540]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">Clystopsenella</emphasis>
Kieffer
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EA9EDA8EFF91FFB50CEAF9CAFA2BFEFB" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" type="key">
<keyStep id="197091A0FF91FFB60CEAF9CAFA2BF970" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB60CEAF9CAFA2AF9D8" blockId="1.[151,1437,1582,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF91FFB60CEAF9CAFA2AF9D8" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
1. Head longer than its maximum width; frontal line indicated as deep sulcus extending from clypeus to anterior ocellus; fore wing membrane with distinct dark spots around apex of radial and marginal cells; distal margin of pterostigma, within marginal cell, straight (early-Miocene Dominican amber)................................................. 
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB608A1F98DFA2AF9D8" bold="true" box="[1244,1437,1640,1663]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
† 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF91FFB60895F98DFA2AF9D8" authority="Engel" authorityName="Engel" authorityYear="2015" box="[1256,1437,1640,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB60895F98DFAEBF9D8" bold="true" box="[1256,1372,1640,1662]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">C. mirabilis</emphasis>
Engel
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB60CEAF963FA2BF970" blockId="1.[151,1437,1582,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF91FFB60CEAF963FA2BF970" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">- Head shorter than its maximum width; frontal line indicated as deep sulcus only near level of antennal foramina; fore wing mostly hyaline, membrane only with yellowish translucent band across region of pterostigma; distal margin of pterostigma, within marginal cell, outcurved (extant fauna).............................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="197091A0FF91FFB60CEAF93AFA2BF867" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB60CEAF93AFA2BF8ED" blockId="1.[151,1437,1582,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF91FFB60CEAF93AFA2BF8ED" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
2. Occipital carina weakly indicated laterally; medial portion of clypeus forming short lobe, its anterior margin incurved; sublateral tooth of clypeus small, less prominent than lateral acetabular lobe; medial elevation of sternum V low and lacking bare triangular declivity; coxae, trochanters and femora mostly brown and tibiae and tarsi light reddish brown (
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF91FFB608A1F8FDFA80F889" box="[1244,1335,1817,1839]" name="Australia" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">Australia</collectingCountry>
)................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF91FFB60811F8D2FA2BF8ED" authority="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2021" box="[1132,1436,1846,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="australiana">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB60811F8D2FA2BF8ED" bold="true" box="[1132,1436,1846,1868]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB60811F8D2FB4EF8EA" bold="true" box="[1132,1273,1846,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">C. australiana</emphasis>
Lepeco &amp; Melo
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB60CEAF8B0FA2BF867" blockId="1.[151,1437,1582,2015]" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF91FFB60CEAF8B0FA2BF867" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
- Occipital carina completely absent; clypeus very short, lacking medial lobe (except in males of 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF91FFB608FDF8B0FAA7F8CF" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[1152,1296,1876,1897]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF91FFB608FDF8B0FAA7F8CF" box="[1152,1296,1876,1897]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">C. longiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which have a short lobe); sublateral tooth of clypeus well developed, more prominent than lateral acetabular lobe; medial elevation of sternum V distinctly pronounced and with bare triangular declivity; legs entirely light reddish brown or yellowish (South America and continental Central America)........................................................................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="197091A0FF91FFB50CEAF82DFA2BFEFB" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF91FFB50CEAF82DFA2BFF4E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1582,2015]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,349]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF91FFB50CEAF82DFA2BFF4E" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="127" pageId="1" pageNumber="126">
3. Frons sparsely punctate, punctures on surface between eye and median line with interspaces exceeding diameter of anterior ocellus, becoming denser near antennal foramina; mesoscutum sparsely punctate between notauli, distance between punctures exceeding diameter of anterior ocellus; mesepisternum slightly depressed dorsad of mesepisternal pit; antennae with homogeneous dark brown coloration (South America and continental Central America).................. 
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB508C1FF36FA2BFF4E" authority="Kieffer" authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1911" box="[1212,1436,210,232]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiventris">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB508C1FF36FA2BFF4E" bold="true" box="[1212,1436,210,232]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB508C1FF36FAFAFF4E" bold="true" box="[1212,1357,210,232]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">C. longiventris</emphasis>
Kieffer
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A23B8905FF92FFB50CEAFF14FA2BFEFB" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<keyLead id="19752A30FF92FFB50CEAFF14FA2BFEFB" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
- Frons densely punctate, punctures on surface between eye and median line with interspaces not exceeding diameter of anterior ocellus; mesoscutum densely punctate between notauli, distance between punctures not exceeding diameter of anterior ocellus; mesepisternum not depressed dorsad of mesepisternal pit, posteriorly with shallow sulcus between pit and posterior edge of sclerite; scape and pedicel yellowish, flagellum light brown (western 
<collectingCountry id="DA93C995FF92FFB50F01FEACFC50FEFB" box="[892,999,327,349]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
)................... 
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB508A2FEA3FA2BFEFB" bold="true" box="[1247,1436,327,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">
<taxonomicName id="6584F286FF92FFB508A2FEA3FAFDFEFB" authority="Lepeco &amp; Melo, 2022" authorityName="Lepeco &amp; Melo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1247,1354,327,349]" class="Insecta" family="Scolebythidae" genus="Clystopsenella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pacifica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="90F05517FF92FFB508A2FEA3FAFDFEFB" bold="true" box="[1247,1354,327,349]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="127">C. pacifica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="8BC3E86CFF92FFB5092DFEACFA2BFEFB" box="[1360,1436,328,349]" pageId="2" pageNumber="127" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
